{
  "stem": "21626.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Never mind, I thought.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "They looked a nice jam there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And when they said marmalade, which in Czech means jam, I thought, great.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And I put lashings of what I thought was sweet jam.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And it turned out to be orange marmalade.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And I couldn't-- I just could not swallow a single mouthful.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And I was so hungry.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And I didn't know what to do.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I put a napkin on my lap.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And every time they weren't looking, I popped a bit of the bread onto the napkin and then later on flushed the whole lot down the loo and looked forward to eating the Czech bread, which was left in my rucksack.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But unfortunately, the leader of the transport, who was also staying there, had gave, gave instructions for Czech food to be destroyed, that now we are in England, we're going to eat English food only.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was devastated, and I was very cross with him.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I thought he was very badly behaved young man because we Czechs always said that bread is sacred and you must never waste any.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And in, in fact, if we dropped a piece of bread, we had to kiss it.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And so I was most, most indignant.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I quite forgot what I did with the English bread, how that ended.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Anyway, my little English mummy, who next month is celebrating her 100th birthday, came to fetch, fetch me in Bloomsbury House two days later.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I can remember that day as if it was yesterday because I was taken into an empty room and left standing there.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
